    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-10-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="445"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr
                        Bigelotc</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 287.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-10-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 19, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Referring to your despatch of the 28th of March
                    last, No. 66, relative to the claim of the Arizona Mining Company against
                    France, on account of the seizure of a quantity of powder on the schooner
                    William L. Richardson, I now transmit to you a copy of a communication of the
                    17th instant, from Messrs. Lewis &amp; Cox, attorneys for that company. As it
                    appears from the evidence that the powder in question was not intended for
                    hostile purposes, and was destined to a place within the jurisdiction of the
                    United States, I must request you to submit the claim to the reconsideration of
                    the imperial government, and to support it by such arguments as the facts of the
                    case may, in your judgment, warrant.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
